ure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"h-8-water-gardens\">8. Water Gardens<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>While you&#x2019;re on your cycle, stop off at the Water Gardens: a beautiful aquatic park filled with water lilies and lotus flowers from all over the world. Wander through the gardens, crossing Japanese bridges, and enjoying the 500 meters of walkways on the banks of the Dordogne river.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How to get there: <\/strong>If you&#x2019;re not a fan of traveling on two wheels, you can drive to the park from Sarlat in under 20 minutes.<br><strong>Entry fee:<\/strong> 8.50 EUR&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--tip \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--tip\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\">Note:<\/strong> the gardens are only open during the summer months May to September from 10 AM &#x2013; 7 PM (11 &#x2013; 6 during September)<\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/19161139\/sarlat-france14.jpg\" alt=\"sarlat france water gardens\n\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"sarlat france water gardens\n\" class=\"wp-image-61637 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/19161139\/sarlat-france14.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/19161139\/sarlat-france14-480x600.jpg 480w, htt